Ex.) "MTG*" will only return "MTG Strategy"

rpcStatus.description:
The `Status` type defines a logical error model that is suitable for
different programming environments, including REST APIs and RPC APIs. It is
used by [gRPC](https://github.com/grpc). Each `Status` message contains
three pieces of data: error code, error message, and error details.

You can find out more about this error model and how to work with it in the
[API Design Guide](https://cloud.google.com/apis/design/errors).

code.description: The status code, which should be an enum value of [google.rpc.Code][google.rpc.Code].

message.description:
A developer-facing error message, which should be in English. Any
user-facing error message should be localized and sent in the
[google.rpc.Status.details][google.rpc.Status.details] field, or localized by the client.

details.description:
A list of messages that carry the error details.  There is a common set of
message types for APIs to use.

v1FilterStrategiesByPatternQuery.title: Represents query to pattern match strategies

strategyNamePattern.description:
Represents strategy name pattern.
Name pattern here uses "*" to allow matching for that pattern anywhere within the strategy name.

expireDate.description:
Represents expire date. If provided, strategies with expire date greater than or 
equal to given date will be returned.

includeExpired.title:
Represents flag to include expired strategies in the result. If expire_date is
provided, this flag will be ignored
(-- api-linter: core::0142::time-field-names=disabled
    aip.dev/not-precedent: We need to do this because expired is a resource state. --)

v1FilterStrategiesByPatternRequest.description: Represents request to pattern match strategies.

pageSize.description:
The maximum number of Strategies to return. The service may
return fewer than this value. If unspecified, at most 100
Strategies will be returned. The maximum value is 100; values
above 100 will be coerced to 100.

pageToken.description:
A page token, received from a previous 'ListStrategies' call.
Provide this to retrieve the subsequent page.
When paginating, all other parameters provided to
'ListStrategies' must match the call that provided the page
token.

v1FilterStrategiesByPatternResponse.description: Filters strategies based on a strategy name pattern. The (*) character can be used as a wildcard. If no wildcard is used, all strategies starting with the provided string will be returned. For example, "MTG" will return "MTG Strategy" whereas "*MTG*" will both "MTG Strategy” as well as "Strategy MTG".

nextPageToken.description:
A token, which can be sent as 'page_token' to retrieve the next page.
If this field is omitted, there are no subsequent pages.

v1Strategy.description: Represents investment strategy referred to by orders and trades.

id.description: The numeric ID of the strategy. This value is system-generated and should not be included in the request.

strategyName.description:
The name of the strategy. If the strategy has a parent, it has to be prefixed and separated by colon.
Example strategy name - US : BONDS (US is parent strategy and US : BONDS together is the strategy name).

expireDate.description: The expiration date of the Strategy. If omitted this will default to 2222-12-31.

startDate.title: The start date of the strategy

expireDate.description:
Represents expire date. If provided, strategies with expire date greater than or 
equal to given date will be returned.

includeExpired.title:
Represents flag to include expired strategies in the result. If expire_date is
provided, this flag will be ignored
